[201.474484, "o", "# Checkpoint Resume Bug Fix Summary\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nThe pipeline script would crash partway through processing 50k JSON records, and despite writing a checkpoint file, it would reprocess everything from the beginning on restart instead of resuming from where it left off.\r\n\r\n## Root Causes Found\r\n\r\n### 1. **Critical: Checkpoint saved batch number, but code compared it to line number**\r\n- **Bug**: `save_checkpoint(batch_num)` saved the batch count (0-49) but `if i < start_from` compared it to line index\r\n- **Impact**: If batch_num=1 (1000 records processed), only 1 line was skipped on resume\r\n- **Fix**: Changed to save and compare actual line numbers (`line_num = i + 1`)\r\n\r\n### 2. **Data Loss: INSERT OR REPLACE overwrote aggregates instead of accumulating**\r\n- **Bug**: `INSERT OR REPLACE` would overwrite existing category totals on resume\r\n- **Impact**: Resumed runs would lose previously aggregated data\r\n- **Fix**: Changed to `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE` to accumulate values:\r\n  ```sql\r\n  INSERT INTO summa"]
[201.474576, "o", "ry (category, total_value, count) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\r\n  ON CONFLICT(category) DO UPDATE SET\r\n      total_value = total_value + excluded.total_value,\r\n      count = count + excluded.count\r\n  ```\r\n\r\n### 3. **Checkpoint File Not Flushed: Race condition on crash**\r\n- **Bug**: `json.dump({'last_line': batch_num}, open('.checkpoint', 'w'))` didn't flush buffer\r\n- **Impact**: Checkpoint might not be written to disk before crash\r\n- **Fix**: Used context manager with explicit flush and fsync:\r\n  ```python\r\n  with open('.checkpoint', 'w') as f:\r\n      json.dump({'last_line': line_num}, f)\r\n      f.flush()\r\n      os.fsync(f.fileno())\r\n  ```\r\n\r\n### 4. **No Intermediate Commits: All work lost on crash**\r\n- **Bug**: `conn.commit()` only called at end of processing\r\n- **Impact**: Database changes lost if process killed before completion\r\n- **Fix**: Added `conn.commit()` after each batch\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\nRan comprehensive test:\r\n1. Processed 8,000 records, killed process\r\n2. Verified checkpoint at line 8000\r\n3. Resumed processin"]
[201.474616, "o", "g\r\n4. Verified final total: exactly 50,000 records (no duplicates)\r\n\r\n## Files Modified\r\n- `process.py` - Fixed all four bugs listed above\r\n- Created `test_checkpoint_resume.sh` - Automated test script\r\n- Backed up original to `process.py.bak`\r\n"]
